nd freeze.";i:9;s:98:"A common cause of a garage door that wont close or open during cold weather is a frozen threshold.";i:10;s:75:"This event happens when the ground is wet usually from rain and it freezes.";i:11;s:131:"If you believe that your garage door is stuck due to being frozen its important not to try opening it until youve cleared the area.";i:12;s:106:"Garage door systems include rollers that enable the door to move along the tracks when opening or closing.";i:13;s:76:"The rollers require lubrication to facilitate the smooth efficient movement.";i:14;s:63:"However cold weather can freeze the lubricant which may result.";i:15;s:88:"When it gets cold I need to hold the button on the wall to get the garage door to close.";i:16;s:47:"Remotes dont work for closing only for opening.";i:17;s:115:"Ive checked the door manually and it moves up and down fine and the sensor is clear and appears to be working fine.";i:18;s:208:"Garage Door Will Not Close All The Way Leaves Gap At Bottom why does garage door not close in cold weather is important information accompanied by photo and HD pictures sourced from all websites in the world.";i:19;s:92:"Download this image for free in High-Definition resolution the choice download button below.";i:20;s:40:"If you do not find the exact resolution.";i:21;s:60:"Garage Door Will Not Close All The Way Leaves Gap At Bottom.";i:22;s:189:"Problems and repairs 5 reasons your garage door won t open in cold weather diy fi garage door will not stay down in cold weather garage door will not close all the way leaves gap at bottom.";i:23;s:27:"Leave a Reply Cancel reply.";i:24;s:89:"When cold they take muck more effort to torque and the drive might not have enough oomph.";i:25;s:51:"Like other poster said set motor adjustment to max.";i:26;s:106:"When the door is released from the drive track it should both lift and shut with equal amount of pressure.";i:27;s:73:"In NapervilleIL the Garage Door Wont Close cold weather issues - YouTube.";i: